# Environment template for the Zapp Global Philosophy School platform.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      # then fill in real values
#
# `.env` is gitignored (this template is NOT) — NEVER commit real secrets.
# Backend vars map 1:1 to `backend/app/config.py` Settings fields (uppercased) and are
# loaded by pydantic-settings; the same file is layered into docker-compose via
# `env_file: .env` and overrides the compose `${VAR:-default}` interpolation defaults.
# PydanticAI is MULTI-PROVIDER: the agent talks to whatever provider your model strings
# (ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL / WORKER_MODEL / JUDGE_MODEL) name — Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini,
# Groq, Mistral, etc. Set ONLY the provider API key that matches those strings; the rest
# stay blank. The backend boots + migrates + serves stub /chat with NO LLM key at all.
# Frontend `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars are BUILD-TIME inlined into the browser bundle — they are
# public by definition, so never put a secret behind a `NEXT_PUBLIC_` name.
#
# req: platform-scaffold-017

# ── Backend (required) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only DATABASE_URL + ADMIN_TOKEN are required for the backend to construct settings
# and boot (no LLM key needed for migrations or the stub /chat path).
#
# Async Postgres DSN (asyncpg driver). Host `db` is the docker-compose service name;
# use `localhost` instead when running uvicorn directly on the host.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://zapp:zapp@db:5432/zapp
# Shared secret guarding admin-only endpoints.
ADMIN_TOKEN=change-me-admin

# ── LLM (PydanticAI, provider-agnostic) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Model strings are provider-prefixed: "<provider>:<model>" (e.g. anthropic:claude-...,
# openai:gpt-..., gemini:gemini-...). Leave blank to fall back to config.py defaults.
ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL=
WORKER_MODEL=
JUDGE_MODEL=
#
# Provider API keys — ALL OPTIONAL. Set ONLY the one matching the provider in your model
# strings above; PydanticAI reads the matching key straight from the environment. Leaving
# them blank is fine when /chat is the stub (no live LLM call).
#   - Other providers PydanticAI supports use their own env keys too, e.g.
#     GROQ_API_KEY, MISTRAL_API_KEY — add whichever your model strings need.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ── Backend (optional observability / geo) ────────────────────────────────────
# Blank or absent = feature initializes in safe no-op mode (no error).
LOGFIRE_TOKEN=
POSTHOG_KEY=
IPINFO_TOKEN=

# ── Frontend (build-time; NEVER secrets) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Browser-facing backend URL. Under compose the browser reaches the host-published
# port, so this is localhost:8000 (not the in-network `backend` hostname).
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
# Public PostHog project key for client-side analytics (blank = analytics disabled).
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
